content: I think I'll focus on finishing the data science course first, and then move on to the machine learning course. I've already invested 6 weeks into the data science course, and I don't want to lose momentum. Plus, finishing one course at a time will help me feel more accomplished and motivated. By the way, do you think listening to a 10-part podcast series on AI in just one week is too fast? I'm worried that I might have missed some important details.
